text.tspan: Once you’ve got Blink working you can add a series of 104 and 22 rated capacitors to
protect your shrimp from power surges. With these extra capacitors we can smooth
out power spikes that might fry the arduino chip otherwise and it just makes things a
bit more robust. Study the 2 diagrams below to add the 6 capacitors rated 22 & 104
nanoFarad and a bigger 10uF capacitor; note this needs to be connected with the white
negative stripe facing the ground cable on G9. Note
Its tricky as it requires components sharing breadboard holes but worth completing.
